<paragraph blockId="21.[189,310,738,764]" box="[189,310,738,764]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,738,764]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,738,764]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1398,785,846]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Both the female and male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann, 2014" authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[527,686,785,812]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteistigma" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[527,686,785,812]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. luteistigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[693,784,786,812]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from all other species of this group by the bright yellowish stigma (
<figureCitation box="[561,672,820,846]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs 11A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[685,739,820,846]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
