<paragraph blockId="21.[189,334,1457,1483]" box="[189,334,1457,1483]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1457,1483]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1457,1483]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,506,1504,1565]" box="[234,325,1504,1530]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,1504,1530]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,506,1504,1565]" box="[189,506,1538,1565]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,501,1538,1565]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="4.85" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1604,1771]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[802,907,1639,1665]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus slightly convex with sparse fine and shallow punctation (i = 2–3 d); surface between punctures apically superficial and shiny, basally distinctly reticulate and matt (
<figureCitation box="[537,618,1709,1736]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
C–D). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally light brown, ventrally yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[666,772,1745,1771]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1810,1978]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures densely reticulate, matt; disc sparsely (i = 3–5 d) and shallowly punctate (
<figureCitation box="[710,791,1845,1871]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
E–F). Metanotum slightly shorter than basal area of propodeum, apically with narrow carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[826,929,1880,1907]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11F</figureCitation>
). Propodeum broadly but finely carinate (
<figureCitation box="[198,302,1916,1942]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11F</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[489,597,1951,1977]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1298,267,294]" box="[189,1298,267,294]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
WINGS. Yellowish-brown; wing venation yellowish-brown, stigma bright yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1285,267,293]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1399,333,394]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore and mid tibia basally with small yellowish spot. Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1398,433,495]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga narrowly translucent yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,309,469,495]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1–T4 without hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1385,469,495]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" startId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" targetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" targetPageId="22">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1399,1926,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,279,1926,1952]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann, 2014" authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[285,521,1926,1953]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteistigma" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[285,521,1926,1953]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Scrapter luteistigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[528,620,1927,1953]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♀. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[668,689,1926,1952]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[861,880,1927,1953]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">B</emphasis>
. Metasoma (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1191,1212,1926,1952]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C</emphasis>
. Head. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1302,1323,1927,1953]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">D</emphasis>
. Head (SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,300,1962,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E</emphasis>
. Thorax (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[570,588,1962,1988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">F</emphasis>
. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1398,267,329]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae yellowish-brown. Terga impunctate, densely sculptured and matt; T2–T4 with indistinct, narrow apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[842,949,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,231,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,554,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,554,1886]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860618/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,506,368,430]" box="[234,298,368,394]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,368,394]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,506,368,430]" box="[189,506,403,430]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,501,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="4.55" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" startId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" targetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" targetPageId="23">
<paragraph blockId="23.[187,1398,1860,1922]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[187,279,1860,1886]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann, 2014" authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[284,521,1860,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteistigma" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[284,521,1860,1887]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Scrapter luteistigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[528,620,1861,1887]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[666,687,1860,1886]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,878,1861,1887]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">B</emphasis>
. Antenna. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1002,1023,1860,1886]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">C</emphasis>
. Metasoma (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1333,1354,1861,1887]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">D</emphasis>
. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[431,451,1896,1922]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E</emphasis>
. Hind tibia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[598,616,1896,1922]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">F</emphasis>
. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,267,364]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face densely covered with long, greyish-white, erect hair. Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antennal flagellum bright yellowish-orange, medioapically broadened (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1137,338,364]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1398,403,500]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc impunctate, strongly and densely sculptured, completely matt. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[315,424,473,500]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1363,539,566]" box="[189,1363,539,566]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation yellowish-brown, stigma bright yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1350,539,565]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,604,701]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
LEGS. Integument black, tarsi, tibiae and femora apically yellow, tibia on both sides with darker spots of variable size (
<figureCitation box="[353,495,640,666]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12A, E</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia basally slightly curved, apically broadened and with a dense tuft of short, white hair on the inside (
<figureCitation box="[593,699,675,701]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
). Vestiture greyish-white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,740,907]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga narrowly translucent yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1386,740,766]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
). T1 medially, T2 densely and following terga successively less covered with short, appressed scale-like hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[781,889,811,837]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
). Terga impunctate, densely sculptured and matt; terga with narrow apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[791,903,846,872]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
). S3–S5 without conspicuous apical hair fringes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1079,946,973]" box="[189,1079,946,973]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
TERMINALIA. S7 (
<figureCitation box="[384,491,946,973]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
) and terminal plate of S8 (
<figureCitation box="[804,906,946,973]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[187,230,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,485,1816]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[189,1399,484,1817]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Scrapter luteistigma sp. nov., ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Antenna. C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860620/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12F</figureCitation>
) as illustrated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,342,1012,1038]" box="[189,342,1012,1038]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1012,1038]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1012,1038]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1398,1058,1120]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
The species is only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[631,682,1059,1085]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Knersvlakte, a semi-desert plane in southern Namaqualand.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,337,1159,1185]" box="[189,337,1159,1185]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,337,1159,1185]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,337,1159,1185]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Floral hosts</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,573,1206,1232]" box="[189,573,1206,1232]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName box="[189,316,1206,1232]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Aizoaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fenzl ex Harv &amp; Sond" authorityYear="1862" box="[327,565,1206,1232]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Galenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sarcophylla">
<emphasis box="[327,565,1206,1232]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Galenia sarcophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,399,1271,1297]" box="[189,399,1271,1297]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,399,1271,1297]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
